    "body": "**Draft until CI confirms this fixes the affected job correctly.**\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n### Problem\r\nThe `i686, no IPC` job [fails](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/actions/runs/25275669000/job/74105140405#step:11:2951) in `sock_tests` at the first [`socket(AF_INET, SOCK_STREAM, IPPROTO_TCP)` call](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/52c3381fa8f4194f9da7cf69e411602c3c7e161d/src/test/sock_tests.cpp#L33).\r\n\r\nThe failing runner [uses Docker 29.4.2](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/actions/runs/25275669000/job/74105140405#step:7:81), while a comparable passing run [used Docker 29.4.1](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/actions/runs/25249734733/job/74039837293#step:7:81).\r\n\r\nDocker 29.4.2 [changed the default seccomp profile](https://docs.docker.com/engine/release-notes/29/#2942) to block `socketcall(2)`, and the Moby seccomp profile documents the explicit `socketcall` deny rule as returning [`ENOSYS`](https://github.com/moby/profiles/releases/tag/seccomp%2Fv0.2.2).\r\n\r\nThis is relevant to Linux i386 because `socketcall(2)` is the legacy [x86-32 sockets entry point](https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/socketcall.2.html#STANDARDS).\r\n\r\n### Fix\r\nAdd a CTest-level skip for `sock_tests` when Linux i386 cannot create the initial `AF_INET` socket because the container seccomp profile blocks the 32-bit socket syscall path.\r\n\r\nThe skip handles `ENOSYS` for Docker's explicit `socketcall(2)` deny rule and `EPERM` for seccomp profiles that use the default errno.\r\n\r\n### Alternative\r\nA potential alternative would be to run the CI container with `--security-opt seccomp=unconfined`, which Docker documents at https://docs.docker.com/engine/security/seccomp/#run-without-the-default-seccomp-profile\r\n\r\nThat is broader because it disables Docker's default seccomp profile for the whole CI container.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nFixes https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/35199.",
