        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree b67d0c5a5125ed688dbd783a137c3b701bd611a6\nparent 8f4a3ba8972dae9412ba975a040cea22c227f983\nauthor Lőrinc <pap.lorinc@gmail.com> 1777815407 +0200\ncommitter Lőrinc <pap.lorinc@gmail.com> 1777817291 +0200\n\ntest: skip sock_tests when socketcall is blocked\n\nDocker 29.4.2 blocks `socketcall(2)` in the default seccomp profile:\nhttps://docs.docker.com/engine/release-notes/29/#2942\nhttps://github.com/moby/profiles/releases/tag/seccomp%2Fv0.2.2\nhttps://github.com/moby/moby/pull/52501\n\n`socketcall(2)` is relevant to Linux i386 socket wrappers:\nhttps://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/socketcall.2.html#STANDARDS\n\nThat can make `sock_tests` fail at the first `socket(AF_INET, SOCK_STREAM, IPPROTO_TCP)` call in the i686 CI job.\nEmit the existing CTest skip marker for `ENOSYS`, matching Moby's explicit deny rule, and keep `EPERM` for profiles that use the default seccomp errno.\n",
        "signature": "-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\niQIzBAABCAAdFiEEqXy8dDLWkKQdUrTAZp//D/pHenYFAmn3VssACgkQZp//D/pH\nenbSmA/+JtXMVLQecLvFj5MYv97O2K+IvqTyo02ZDwVf7i+6A0B/bYU93kFas/BA\nXkpzr5Dg/t5IP9s9mqRh3geEOMkjy5DuO+OXbU/bUACMtelSKmGsIY58p1xQ4drM\nVDvjXrK9KpSVYvBuk7awaEUgj9xW1sGUyC9btazm3SJQdsAV+EVHq3P7y5UOM+oT\n3JAvB3vOEml6nqvv0SUQTH6/q8/geGxojX5rZtkFjgOOh11ZM8NmDviQhmgrc8vp\ndy+N8g8iRUzYgdL3S0Z73rO0Nu7WixBlyWcR2Dgg5a+bdJBfrSlc6SdFcQRizbao\nbMkppM543lLYQaKEZLPQhUkn6ZIC9mub/2B6Sr2yM8rcOCv1/0yOc3zZUokppwjw\ncNHASoAzsWMbTqwQXBH1uOoPSzuXbo+MEYfXjOzCrUe4FfhbQkh7vpu8yGflD6Ld\nXLpOeMNjjr1nAmMqOvDnC9s2dp2G+BIdBALvmA6zo8SXx2zMXyIYxd1as5dYlczP\nOlv+7WWey8+veihFUHxRYN9+SjBFUiDiTgevaMNl35nq59Ob8JX9I1jjpyYZEP59\n1tvr88kIPJ6evAX9499PlpQT9nDmk9wc4ruuRrVbv6hE8FBUjfcrbRYiclgk3m2s\nFpTpjxDXF8BeesvlqWI1IGU53svJb9r17I47PjDanaUFI8tVGl8=\n=9RbD\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----"
